    <abstract id="aspace_c4a0f67d8b892c860fcd1734094490d5">This collection was assembled by gallery owner Theodore Bonin, containing 61 artworks and publications from over 20 artists including Tom Otterness, Lisa Bowman, Judy Rifka, Janine Antoni, and Luis Frangella, who were active in New York's downtown art scene during the 1980s and 1990s. Artwork mediums include hand colored and painted works on paper, wood sculpture, ceramic sculptures, prints, and assemblages.</abstract>
    <langmaterial id="aspace_9b1eb7144469a6e3a6694eb88135fb1e">Materials are in English.</langmaterial>
  </did>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_dd0145ac1b13339cbc178b6ff507e38b">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>This collection contains 61 artworks and publications, accumulated by Theodore Bonin over many years, from over 20 artists including Tom Otterness, Lisa Bowman, Judy Rifka, Janine Antoni, and Luis Frangella, who were active in New York's downtown art scene during the 1980s and 1990s. Artwork media represented in this collection include painted or drawn works on paper, wood sculpture, ceramic sculptures, prints, and assemblages, all produced during the 1980s and 1990s. This collection illustrates popular mediums and subject matter in artworks in this community of artists in New York.</p>  </scopecontent>
